I had my brother over for dinner and he ate HALF of the pozole himself! The green pumkin seeds, or pepitas, are an important ingredient. Most supermarkets these days have a Mexican/Latin spice section, you'll find them there. Otherwise, go to a local tienda (Mexican grocer), if there's one in your area. I used bone-in thighs for a more robust broth, added epazote *and* oregano, and like everyone else, more hominy. The accompaniments are crucial - don't skimp on them!

